Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: that is a beast, for 1500 sq ft. I am dealing with 100sq ft and it must be on a wall, about ~9ft high near the interior roof line

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: I have been reading a lot about hot isle containment, that datacenter people write about. It's fascinating stuff

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: so the plan is to suck in cold air from under the building at the floor, and push the hottest air out at the top near the roof line

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: and i will have some kind of tent/containment system to isolate hot exhaust air and funnel it up and out

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it can easily get 110F outside here, and unfortunately my structure gets full sun during part of the day. Heat is my biggest issue
